=================================================================== 
PART 1 - Disc Creation - Can be performed any time
=================================================================== 
1. Find Server, edit properties and add new hard disk
2. Take online new disk, Initialize it in GPT mode and assign letter X:\ 
3. Run robocopy command 
robocopy E:\ X:\ /MIR /SEC /SECFIX /MT:16 /NP /TEE /log+:C:\Temp\robocopy.log
 E:\ - source 
X:\ - destination 
4. Wait for moving files

==============================================================================
 Part 2 - Disk letter changing - this should be performed OOH
==============================================================================
1. Open computer management, find disk E:\ "Change drive letter and paths", 
2. Select E: and change it to Z:\ 
3. Sync files by running 
robocopy Z:\ E:\ /MIR /SEC /SECFIX /MT:16 /NP /TEE /log+:C:\Temp\robocopy_sync.log
4. Find disc X:\ and change letter to E:\ 

=========================================================================== 
Part 3 - Old disk deletion - should be performed after few days
===========================================================================
1. Delete old disk from virtualization side
===========================================================================

Revert

1. Change letter of the new disk with letter E:\ to X:\, and then rename old disk with letter Z:\ back to letter E:\
2. Delete newly created disk
